Version 0.5.0 (2018-06-19)
--------------------------

Features
~~~~~~~~

* implementation for ansible orchestrator

Version 0.4.0 (2018-04-25)
--------------------------

Features
~~~~~~~~

* do not require floating ip for openstack resources.
* carbon's own time mixin class.
* ability to run carbon framework as a container.
* apache libcloud openstack provider support.

Bug Fixes
~~~~~~~~~

* only allow beaker config to be created once.
* lock ansible version until carbon supports latest ansible.
* always save the beaker job id in carbon results file.
* unable to locate kickstart file during beaker provisioning.

Chore
~~~~~

* python 3 support for openstack provider module.
* remove need to define openstack tenant id.
* add make targets for building/deploying container images.
* remove code regarding docker implementation for carbon.
* update dockerfile for carbon.
* clean up unused modules, tests, etc from code base.
* set the default openstack provisioner to use apache libcloud.
* split requirements.txt into multiple requirements.txt files.
* convert function checking git urls to be a generic url checker.
* provide support for ansible greater than 2.4.
* integration test improvements.
* update Beaker container to have mounted volume.
* update OpenShift container to have mounted volume.

Documentation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* updating the Beaker documentation to reference bkr_kickstart as an asset.
* describing assets for Beaker and OpenShift providers
* updating the assets keys to be consistent throughout the doc.
* only show one authentication type for beaker examples.

Refactor
~~~~~~~~

* log node state when waiting for node to finish building.
* refactor OpenShift provisioning/deleting to run locally.
* refactor beaker provisioner to run beaker client calls locally.
* simplify the method for creating loggers.

Tests
~~~~~

* enable and revise beaker provisioner functional tests.
* adds revised beaker provisioner integration tests.
* adds revised openshift provisioner integration tests.
* update openstack provider integration tests.


